I explained above why Apple's old guard =E2=80=94 particularly the most sen=
ior members who remember the 90s =E2=80=94 are an obstacle to unleashing de=
velopers. Implicit in "old guard", however, is just plain "old", and AI is =
very much a young person's game. It requires such a different way of thinki=
ng and approach to product development, and it's reasonable to wonder if Ap=
ple, at least at the leadership level, has it in them.

To that end, I am somewhat surprised =E2=80=94 and disappointed =E2=80=94 t=
hat last week's news about Siri's delay did not include any news about exec=
utive retirements; there was news in January ( https://www.bloomberg.com/ne=
ws/articles/2025-01-24/apple-enlists-company-veteran-kim-vorrath-to-help-fi=
x-ai-and-siri ) about an executive shuffle in the AI team, but this failure=
 strikes me as one that is significant enough to demand accountability.

